      "content": "Mechanistically, many CYP2D6 inhibitors bind in the active site such that:\n- A **protonated amine** forms a strong ionic interaction with **Asp301**.\n- Aromatic groups align in hydrophobic regions near the heme, blocking substrate access or altering catalytic positioning.",
      "tool_name": null,
