      "content": "This molecule likely:\n- Can provide **hydrophobic/aromatic interactions** (phenyl/pyridine).\n- But **cannot reliably provide the key ionic interaction** because it lacks a **protonatable tertiary amine**; amide nitrogens won\u2019t protonate, and pyridine is a weaker/less consistently protonated anchor.\n- The **two amide carbonyls** may also favor conformations/solvation that reduce deep, tight binding in the CYP2D6 pocket.",
